  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed across inlet boundary conditions and blood viscosity parameters using a Latin hypercube sampling approach; a screening sensitivity study was also conducted to characterize input variability effects on the relative hemolysis index, confirming that flow rate and impeller speed account for the majority of output variance. UQ results are reported in the accompanying technical memorandum.",
