      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence study with GCI < 5% on the primary QoI (RH index) at the worst-case operating point.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed at 3 L/min, 3500 RPM. Meshes of 4.2M, 8.7M, and 17.1M cells used. Richardson extrapolation yielded GCI of 3.1% on RH index, satisfying the 5% threshold. Production mesh set at 8.7M cells as optimal accuracy-cost balance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions documented and traceable to CFD boundary conditions; fluid properties and operating parameters match within 5%.",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions from the FDA benchmark protocol were reproduced: bovine blood analog (glycerol-water, viscosity 3.5 mPa·s at 37°C), flow rates measured with Coriolis meter (±1.5%), rotational speed verified with optical tachometer (±10 RPM). CFD boundary conditions set to match measured experimental values."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison of predicted vs. measured RH index at all five operating points with documented error metrics.",
      "rationale": "Predicted RH index compared against experimental measurements at all five operating points. Mean absolute percentage error 8.3%, maximum 14.1% at 6 L/min. Experimental uncertainty (±12%) overlaps model predictions at all points. Comparison performed using both normalized and absolute error metrics per ASME V&V 40 Table 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstrated that RH index computed from CFD stress-exposure integral is the appropriate surrogate for clinical hemolysis at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "RH index derived from Lagrangian particle tracking of red blood cell stress exposure is the accepted regulatory surrogate for pump-induced hemolysis per FDA guidance. Correlation with in vitro plasma-free hemoglobin measurements reviewed from published literature. QoI confirmed appropriate for the intended decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
