      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities performed on geometry, flow regime, and fluid properties sufficiently similar to the COU device and operating conditions.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which shares key geometric features (impeller diameter, volute design) with the CPB device under assessment. Operating Reynolds numbers and flow regimes overlap with COU envelope. Differences in impeller blade count documented and assessed as minor for hemolysis prediction purposes."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 beyond code verification activities already completed.",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error assessment beyond discretization and code verification is not required at Model Risk Level 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. Iterative convergence monitored via residual norms (all below 1e-5) and mass imbalance (< 0.01%) for each simulation run."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
