      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; analyst qualification documented separately.",
      "rationale": "Formal use error assessment not required at MRL 2. Simulation analysts hold relevant CFD credentials and completed internal training on hemolysis modeling protocols. Simulation inputs and setup reviewed by independent senior analyst prior to production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; model form selection documented with engineering justification.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published benchmarking for rotary blood pump flows. Model form uncertainty not formally quantified at MRL 2 but selection rationale documented in simulation plan SP-2023-04. Sensitivity to turbulence model choice noted as a topic for future MRL 3 assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs documented with sources and uncertainty ranges; UQ performed over input parameter space to characterize output variability.",
      "rationale": "All model inputs catalogued in input parameter register IPR-2023-11. Uncertainty ranges assigned to six inputs: inlet flow rate (±3%), fluid viscosity (±8%), impeller speed (±0.5%), inlet turbulence intensity (±50% relative), blood damage model power-law coefficients (literature range), and wall roughness (±20%). A 500-sample Latin hypercube UQ study was executed propagating these uncertainties through the hemolysis model. Output variance in RH index reported as ±18% (95th percentile interval). A screening sensitivity study was also described in the UQ technical memorandum TM-UQ-2023-02, identifying flow rate and impeller speed as the largest contributors to output variance based on standardized regression coefficients; however, the structured sensitivity analysis results are summarized narratively within the UQ memorandum and have not been encoded as a linked sensitivity analysis object in this assessment package."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
